Dad,you can't fire him.

72
00:03:40,450 --> 00:03:42,540
I'm telling you it's a
violation of labor rights.

73
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:46,370
Bea,when you have graduated from Harvard
Law,we'll continue this conversation.

74
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:47,900
But Stanton didn't do it.

75
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:51,430
- Elizabeth.
- William.Is this a good time?

76
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,730
Of course.This is my daughter Bea.

77
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,380
I met you when you were a baby.

78
00:03:55,570 --> 00:03:56,690
Mm,I've heard the stories.

79
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:58,980
And I'm not going to law school.

80
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,190
Elizabeth,my apologies.

81
00:04:01,430 --> 00:04:04,040
Bea spends so much time
with her head stuck in novels

82
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,970
that the realities of
life are all the harsher.

83
00:04:07,140 --> 00:04:09,060
Is it true about Stanton?What happened?

84
00:04:09,570 --> 00:04:12,390
He leaked the truth about
my health to the press.

85
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:15,380
It was damaging to my business
and a personal betrayal.

86
00:04:15,820 --> 00:04:19,030
I'm really sorry to
hear that.How are you?

87
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:25,490
Well,blood sugar spikes like the
market,ticker's on Mile 24,but screw the doctors.

88
00:04:25,640 --> 00:04:28,040
Now that Patrick's home,I
feel like I'm 40 again.

89
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,550
And?How is he?

90
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:32,760
Well,he's Patrick.

91
00:04:33,350 --> 00:04:35,730
As you know,art was the
only thing we had in common,

92
00:04:35,870 --> 00:04:38,650
and I'm still hoping
that's a way we can connect.

93
00:04:39,670 --> 00:04:42,140
Liz Mitchell.I'm coming in.

94
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:45,990
Patrick?You're taller.

95
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:47,100
And lost the blue hair.

96
00:04:47,450 --> 00:04:48,520
I like this better.

97
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:50,590
You are as beautiful as ever.

98
00:04:55,310 --> 00:04:58,020
Yeah,that got us kicked out
of the Accademia in Florence.

99
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:01,500
Wow,you still have your scar too.

100
00:05:01,750 --> 00:05:02,870
What was that name of the horse again?

101
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:03,930
- Cheval Chase.
- Yes.

102
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:06,530
Threw me clear over
the fence at Stony Hill.

103
00:05:06,670 --> 00:05:09,370
Mm,and that was the first
time I thought I'd lost you.

104
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:11,810
- I'm gonna go check on Bea.
- Okay.

105
00:05:14,490 --> 00:05:17,060
All right,kid,I've
got a lot of questions.

106
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:22,540
After mom died,I begged dad to let
me stay in the city with him and Bea.

107
00:05:23,330 --> 00:05:24,910
I was so sad about your mom.

108
00:05:26,540 --> 00:05:30,670
Dad wanted me to go to Le
Rosey.But I wasn't ready.

109
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:33,260
- Is that why you ran?
- I was tired of living on his terms.

110
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:36,300
You were just a kid.How did you do it?

111
00:05:36,460 --> 00:05:37,460
Saved my allowance.

112
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,980
On a ski day,I snowboarded
from Zermatt to Cervinia,

113
00:05:41,530 --> 00:05:44,290
sold my gear,hopped on a
train,and never looked back.

114
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:46,350
You put your family through hell.

115
00:05:47,420 --> 00:05:48,480
What made you come back?

116
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:52,520
Dad.Rumors that he was sick
were all over the papers.

117
00:05:53,030 --> 00:05:55,350
I came back for him,not for this life.

118
00:05:56,090 --> 00:05:57,380
He's trying.

119
00:05:58,740 --> 00:05:59,960
By buying me art?

120
00:05:59,970 --> 00:06:03,520
- It's his way of bonding.Let him.
- Okay.

121
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,790
Well,I remember your tastes.

122
00:06:05,170 --> 00:06:10,490
We have Dutch masters,baroque,abstract
expressionists.

123
00:06:10,670 --> 00:06:13,990
That one.The Picasso.

124
00:06:15,450 --> 00:06:16,880
The Homme Au Cornet?

125
00:06:18,810 --> 00:06:19,770
I put this in as a joke.

126
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,040
Do you remember the Reina Sofia?

127
00:06:24,490 --> 00:06:28,540
You called Guernica a bastard
child of cubist-surrealist mentovem

128
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:31,700
and accused Picasso of
crimes against beauty.

129
00:06:33,230 --> 00:06:35,980
I was a kid.Tastes change.

130
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:41,420
- You sure?
- Yeah.I love it.

131
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,700
Well,I'll have the gallery send it over.

132
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,460
Elizabeth.How's Downton Abbey?

133
00:06:58,670 --> 00:07:03,480
I know this is gonna sound weird,but I don't
think Patrick Wolcott is Patrick Wolcott.

134
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:06,750
It's his eyes.They're the right
color,but it doesn't feel like him.

135
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:09,870
- You think he's an imposter?
- So it's possible.

136
00:07:10,010 --> 00:07:11,870
Yeah,missing rich kids are a subset.

137
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:15,560
You got your Patty Hearsts,your
John Paul Gettys,talented Mr.Ripleys.

138
00:07:16,350 --> 00:07:17,980
William Wolcott is a perfect mark.

139
00:07:18,290 --> 00:07:20,570
A very sick,emotionally fragile mark.

140
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:22,160
Will you look into it?

141
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:24,140
Yeah.I have to run it by Peter,but...

142
00:07:24,710 --> 00:07:27,800
- How he's holding up?
- I will find out.

143
00:07:29,820 --> 00:07:30,850
How are you feeling?

144
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:33,390
Tip-top.Million bucks.

145
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:37,740
Even if he is a ringer,you're telling me
William Wolcott wouldn't know his own son?

146
00:07:38,150 --> 00:07:39,940
Emotion is a con man's sweet spot.

147
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:42,670
And I have good reason to believe
that that is not the real Patrick.

148
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,590
- Better be good.
- It is.

149
00:07:43,730 --> 00:07:45,190
- Better be damn good.
- It is.

150
00:07:47,350 --> 00:07:48,920
Does your wife's intuition count?

151
00:07:49,870 --> 00:07:50,940
El called you?

152
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:53,080
I did say you guys were on
the friends and family plan.

153
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:57,940
Is this some elaborate ruse
to avoid the Mortensen case?

154
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:02,240
Okay,that hurts my feelings,because we're
looking at potential identity theft,fraud.

155
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:05,670
A family's fortune is at stake,not
to mention the charitable foundation.

156
00:08:05,910 --> 00:08:08,470
- Based on what?
- Pablo Picasso.

157
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:12,180
Kid hated his work,and now he's
pushing Elizabeth to buy one.

158
00:08:12,340 --> 00:08:16,690
You want me to launch into an
investigation based on a Picasso snafu?

159
00:08:16,820 --> 00:08:19,860
Peter,this is like you
suddenly becoming a Red Sox fan.

160
00:08:20,780 --> 00:08:24,080
- I'd have to be...
- I'm...you'd have to what?

161
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:26,470
- I'd have to be a different person.
- Thank you.

162
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:29,680
- It's hot in here.
- Yeah,you really don't look good.You should go home.

163
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:34,060
I'm not going home.I'm not
sick.I've never gone home sick.

164
00:08:34,220 --> 00:08:36,120
You're gonna have to
give me more than Picasso.

165
00:08:36,310 --> 00:08:39,860
Also suspicious...Mr.Wolcott
fired his butler of over 30 years.

166
00:08:39,980 --> 00:08:41,620
- Good help is hard to find.
- Or he was set up.

167
00:08:41,970 --> 00:08:45,670
The smart move is to jettison anyone
who intimately knew the real Patrick.

168
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:49,420
- We'd need a DNA test.
- His father hasn't ordered one.

169
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,670
But Elizabeth could grab a
hair when she's over there.

170
00:08:52,770 --> 00:08:55,110
Okay,I'm not sending my
wife in as a secret agent.

171
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:56,410
- So send me in.
- How?

172
00:08:56,570 --> 00:08:58,530
The Wolcotts need a
new butler.I can buttle.

173
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,700
- Buttle?
- Yeah,it's a verb.

