220
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:46,760
Mid-century American
fiction.My weakness.

221
00:11:49,150 --> 00:11:49,910
Come on,Chauncey.

222
00:11:50,210 --> 00:11:51,900
- Hey,Bea.
- Hey,Patrick.

223
00:11:54,610 --> 00:11:55,700
Say hi,Chaunce.

224
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,010
How was your ride?

225
00:12:00,730 --> 00:12:03,480
Every morning there's something
else I remember about this city.

226
00:12:03,860 --> 00:12:05,050
May I take your helmet,sir?

227
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:06,940
No,I am gonna fix the strap.

228
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:08,330
May I take your jacket?

229
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:10,900
No,I got it.

230
00:12:10,910 --> 00:12:11,870
You must be thirsty.

231
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:18,990
My father thinks people
need servants.I don't.

232
00:12:19,130 --> 00:12:21,110
- I can take care of myself.
- Of course.

233
00:12:34,970 --> 00:12:39,980
Mr.Wolcott,the Times,Herald,and Guardian
all open to the financial section,

234
00:12:40,190 --> 00:12:42,770
and your Amaranth toast with
almond butter's in the dining room.

235
00:12:42,990 --> 00:12:44,850
