250
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:50,620
You're kicking me out?

251
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:55,950
- No!No,no,no,just...just taking the appropriate medical precautions.
- Okay.

252
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:59,590
You can see the
map,right?Everything's good?

253
00:14:00,210 --> 00:14:02,550
Patrick got out of Germany on a barge.

254
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,030
The family paid a ton in tips.

255
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:06,040
Most of them happened right
after he ran from school.

256
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:12,900
He was first spotted at the
train station in-- Dusseldorf.

257
00:14:13,210 --> 00:14:16,360
Peter,go home.We got this.Okay?

258
00:14:16,570 --> 00:14:19,250
Caffrey is doing his thing.Go home.

259
00:14:19,780 --> 00:14:21,170
Oh,I got my tie.

260
00:14:50,830 --> 00:14:51,880
Nothing.

261
00:14:58,540 --> 00:15:01,470
And it's the bottom
of the eighth inning...

262
00:15:01,620 --> 00:15:04,240
- Neal,hey.
- You sound terrible.Where are you?

263
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:07,470
I'm working from home.

264
00:15:09,330 --> 00:15:11,340
Mr."No Sick Days"" went home."

265
00:15:11,390 --> 00:15:12,490
Did you get the evidence?

266
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:16,000
It's gonna be harder than we thought.

267
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:18,950
I dusted Patrick's glass.He wiped it.

268
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:19,980
You sure about that?

269
00:15:20,110 --> 00:15:25,100
Yeah.Hairbrush is clean.Toothbrush...and
razor are sanitized.

270
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:28,240
The surfaces are spotless.Either
this guy's a total neat freak...

271
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:33,270
Or he has a reason to be living
without leaving a...trace.

272
00:15:33,480 --> 00:15:35,490
Is he this careful all over the house?

273
00:15:35,910 --> 00:15:37,930
Yeah,he wouldn't even
hand me his bike helmet.

274
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:41,630
He's careful.I think Elizabeth's right.

275
00:15:42,150 --> 00:15:44,090
Yeah.She usually is.

276
00:15:45,550 --> 00:15:47,280
- I gotta go.
- He onto you?

277
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:53,040
It looks great,you
guys.Thank you so much.

278
00:16:10,310 --> 00:16:12,900
Sorry,Liz.Didn't mean to scare you.

279
00:16:13,130 --> 00:16:16,180
It's okay.I was just
admiring the Picasso.

280
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:20,410
Remember those guards who
threatened to call The Policia

281
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:23,550
when my manifesto against
cubism got too loud?

282
00:16:25,220 --> 00:16:28,230
And I used every Spanish word
I knew just to charm them.

283
00:16:28,370 --> 00:16:33,440
You promised that we would go to a bullfight
if I kept my mouth shut,which was a lie.

284
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:38,860
But we did go to Tapas at Casa del
Abuelo,and you let me have a cana,

285
00:16:39,040 --> 00:16:42,000
which was sent over by that
matador who took a shine to you.

286
00:16:42,140 --> 00:16:45,170
- Antonio.
- Paco.

287
00:16:46,830 --> 00:16:47,960
It all came back to me.

288
00:16:48,860 --> 00:16:49,730
Eventually.

289
00:16:58,830 --> 00:16:59,900
Sir?

290
00:17:02,690 --> 00:17:03,270
Miss Bea?

291
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:06,880
Would you mind keeping it down a little
bit?I'm working on a genealogy project.

292
00:17:08,140 --> 00:17:11,940
Apologies.I mistook it for snooping.

293
00:17:13,010 --> 00:17:15,760
Seems we have a pot-kettle situation.

294
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:17,440
No comment.

295
00:17:23,030 --> 00:17:27,310
- Find anything interesting?
- Um,travel journal.Fairly informative.

296
00:17:30,170 --> 00:17:33,650
You know,I grew up hearing
all about my brother,

297
00:17:33,870 --> 00:17:38,140
and now that he's actually here,he's
only told me things I already know.

298
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:41,050
Maybe you could ask about his travels.

299
00:17:41,750 --> 00:17:43,530
It doesn't seem like he
really wants to talk to me.

300
00:17:45,860 --> 00:17:46,780
I'm sorry,Miss Bea.

301
00:17:46,980 --> 00:17:50,450
And now Stanton's
fired,and dad's really sick.

302
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:52,200
Soon he'll be gone too.

303
00:17:53,090 --> 00:17:55,770
And then it'll just be me and Patrick.

304
00:17:55,990 --> 00:17:58,170
And you don't want to be left
with someone you don't know.

305
00:18:10,050 --> 00:18:11,020
Why are you in here?

306
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:13,360
I thought you could wear
this to dinner tonight,sir.

307
00:18:14,510 --> 00:18:19,590
Tell my father no matter how many designer
coats he crams in my closet,I'm not wearing one.

308
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:29,220
May I ask,how does a teenager
evade an international search?

309
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,740
Doctored my dorm mates' passports,

310
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:36,550
used 'em to cross borders,and then
traded 'em when I needed supplies.

311
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:38,970
Bartered to conserve cash.Clever.

312
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:41,130
Colored contacts,a baseball cap.

313
00:18:41,280 --> 00:18:43,870
Switched up your accents and
avoided Portofino in July?

314
00:18:44,090 --> 00:18:45,780
Santorini was more my style.

315
00:18:48,730 --> 00:18:50,970
- Is that your journal?
- Tales of my travels.

316
00:18:52,170 --> 00:18:53,360
Looks like it got wet.

317
00:18:55,290 --> 00:18:56,890
Dropped it in the Aegean.

318
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:02,220
- You're lucky,sir.
- Why's that?

319
00:19:02,450 --> 00:19:04,860
After all this,your
father will take you back.

320
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:09,620
Why not put on a jacket,make
the old man happy?

321
00:19:10,180 --> 00:19:11,920
Carlyle,you are something else.

322
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:23,950
Enjoy your dinner.

323
00:19:33,870 --> 00:19:35,120
'Cause I got your print.

324
00:19:44,170 --> 00:19:45,470
Honey,herbal tea.

325
00:19:46,260 --> 00:19:48,160
Okay.And I got ginger.

326
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,220
And oscillococcinum.

327
00:19:51,610 --> 00:19:53,190
I don't eat things that I can't say.

328
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:59,540
At least tell us how you lifted the
cuff link while I eat things I can't say.

329
00:20:02,490 --> 00:20:03,480
PDA.

330
00:20:04,030 --> 00:20:05,320
Public display of affection?

331
00:20:05,510 --> 00:20:06,680
- Elizabeth,can I use your jacket?
- Sure.

332
00:20:07,430 --> 00:20:08,860
I'm not sure I like this.

333
00:20:11,700 --> 00:20:15,170
Clip this to your left sleeve.

334
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:16,460
This is not going to work.

335
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:18,370
Oh,it's gonna work.I'm gonna steal
something right off your wrist.

336
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:20,370
- Watch.
- Oh,I'm watching.

337
00:20:20,690 --> 00:20:22,790
Proximity manipulation.

338
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:25,330
Diversion technique.

339
00:20:26,410 --> 00:20:27,490
Attention control.

340
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:30,840
Proximity,diversion,attention.PDA.

341
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:34,770
It's still there.

342
00:20:36,530 --> 00:20:37,550
From your other wrist.

343
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:39,800
I even told you what I was gonna steal.

344
00:20:39,980 --> 00:20:43,250
Wristwatch.You have a gentle touch.

345
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:44,470
Oh,oh,that's enough.

346
00:20:48,570 --> 00:20:49,120
Hey,Jones.

347
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:51,100
Oh,better.

348
00:20:51,970 --> 00:20:53,530
Got it.Thanks.

349
00:20:55,430 --> 00:20:58,570
Well,do you have a magic trick that
can turn bad news into good news?

350
00:20:58,700 --> 00:20:59,460
Why,what's up?

351
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:02,380
The prints on the
cuff link were perfect,

352
00:21:02,610 --> 00:21:05,840
except they belong to a person
who's never committed a crime.

353
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:08,680
And it wasn't common to fingerprint
kids when Patrick was younger,

354
00:21:08,850 --> 00:21:09,820
so he's not in the database.

355
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,420
I could send it to Quantico
for a mitochondrial DNA test.

356
00:21:13,570 --> 00:21:17,110
That takes too long.I can get some
actual DNA,and we can run the test here.

357
00:21:17,290 --> 00:21:21,810
Return the cuff link and
try my technique..G.A.F.

358
00:21:22,910 --> 00:21:25,260
- G.A.F.
- Grab a fork.

359
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:27,390
Grab
- literally steal the silverware.

360
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:28,740
You're a cliche.

361
00:21:29,990 --> 00:21:30,890
Get over it.

362
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:33,790
He's grumpy when he's sick.Lean back.

363
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,520
- Hey,what's up?
- Oh,hey.Yeah.

364
00:21:49,390 --> 00:21:50,690
How's life on Golden Pond?

365
00:21:52,610 --> 00:21:53,620
And I see you opened the Brunello.

366
00:21:54,370 --> 00:22:01,240
- Oh,yeah,I saved you...Enjoy.
- Thanks.

367
00:22:02,660 --> 00:22:06,610
- Moz.
- Oh,for once I'm not the only one in the room with a buzz.

368
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,540
It's loud for one hive.

369
00:22:08,720 --> 00:22:10,550
I may have acquired three.

370
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:13,700
Skinny Gianetta got nabbed,so
his wife put out feelers.

371
00:22:13,850 --> 00:22:16,830
So in addition to me being undercover
as a butler and taking care of Peter,

372
00:22:16,980 --> 00:22:18,690
I'm now the guardian of orphan bees.

373
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:20,410
What ails the Suit?

374
00:22:21,490 --> 00:22:23,070
It's that flu that's going around.

375
00:22:23,450 --> 00:22:24,650
That's perfect.

376
00:22:25,430 --> 00:22:30,960
It seems fitting that a man of his
persuasion should be my Guinea pig.

377
00:22:32,280 --> 00:22:36,800
18 amino acids packed into an
antimicrobial,flavonoid-filled,

378
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:41,210
honey-based tonic that will rid you
of your symptoms and also cure warts,

379
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:45,810
elevate your mood,and
enhance performance.

380
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:49,690
Thank me later.Or don't.

381
00:22:49,860 --> 00:22:50,720
- Don't.
- Don't.

382
00:22:54,170 --> 00:22:55,720
I'm supposed to drink this?

383
00:22:55,910 --> 00:23:00,740
One now,the second in two hours,and the
third within four hours of the first.

384
00:23:01,070 --> 00:23:02,780
Oh,I must be crazy
to even consider this.

385
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:05,680
- Could you feel any worse?
- Probably not.

386
00:23:10,550 --> 00:23:13,360
I got to get to the
Wolcotts.Feel better,Peter.

387
00:23:14,290 --> 00:23:15,470
I'll stay here and observe.

388
00:23:16,730 --> 00:23:18,450
Observe what?What's gonna happen?

389
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:21,800
Well,the first 15 minutes
- well,let's see.

390
00:23:30,520 --> 00:23:31,990
Well,it's going to happen.

391
00:23:32,230 --> 00:23:33,430
Dad,it's not what I want.

392
00:23:33,610 --> 00:23:35,180
It's what I want.Consider that.

393
00:23:35,390 --> 00:23:36,730
My attorney is sending it over.

394
00:23:39,800 --> 00:23:41,680
- May I take your cup?
- No.

395
00:23:44,970 --> 00:23:45,900
No.

396
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:51,060
So this conversation's over.

397
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:52,220
In my mind it is.

398
00:23:52,850 --> 00:23:54,190
Let's talk about something else.

399
00:23:55,390 --> 00:23:59,300
Did you know that Picasso used
to burn his own work for warmth?

400
00:23:59,740 --> 00:24:01,330
That's right.He did.

401
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:06,480
Sir.

402
00:24:10,450 --> 00:24:12,040
Oh,this was a mistake.

403
00:24:13,050 --> 00:24:14,630
It was supposed to go
to the business manager.

404
00:24:15,390 --> 00:24:16,410
Here you go.

405
00:24:23,910 --> 00:24:25,160
- Thank you.
- Good afternoon.

406
00:24:30,310 --> 00:24:33,020
Time for vial number two.

407
00:24:33,610 --> 00:24:34,670
Where'd Mozzie go?

408
00:24:35,030 --> 00:24:36,520
He needed to check on his queen.

409
00:24:38,020 --> 00:24:39,690
Assuming he meant bee,but with him...

410
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:40,930
You never know.

411
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:47,480
This came for you.

412
00:24:47,620 --> 00:24:50,110
I can't open it.It's
for William Wolcott.

413
00:24:50,190 --> 00:24:51,750
But it's addressed to Peter Burke.

414
00:24:52,560 --> 00:24:57,740
You know,I think your wife had to open
it for you because you're extremely sick.

415
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:05,240
Besides,no one will ever
know.We can just reseal it.

416
00:25:05,500 --> 00:25:07,290
Neal's a very bad influence on you.

417
00:25:11,610 --> 00:25:14,070
- Oh,yes.
- That was perfect.

418
00:25:14,750 --> 00:25:17,880
Neal found out what Patrick's after
- a trust fund.

419
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:21,240
He was supposed to
inherit it when he was 21.

420
00:25:22,100 --> 00:25:24,580
They're redoing the paperwork today.

421
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,500
- $40 million.
- Yeah.

422
00:25:27,310 --> 00:25:29,110
Honey,if he gets
that,he's gonna disappear.

423
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:30,600
William's heart can't take that.

424
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:32,180
I got to let him know what's going on.

425
00:25:32,340 --> 00:25:36,740
No.Bring William to the
FBI.I want to talk to him.

426
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:40,500
I'm not sure what this Patrick is
capable of.He could be dangerous.

427
00:25:40,760 --> 00:25:43,820
Babe,look,this is a hard
conversation to have with a father,

428
00:25:44,010 --> 00:25:46,260
and it needs to come from a
friend.Besides,you need to take it easy.

429
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:47,760
No,I don't want to take it easy.

430
00:25:47,970 --> 00:25:49,210
- I feel better.
- Well,that's great.

431
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:51,690
I'll let you know how it
goes at the Wolcotts',okay?

432
00:25:51,970 --> 00:25:54,480
Besides,I want you to lay down.

433
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:03,800
William,I'm not trying to upset you.

434
00:26:04,230 --> 00:26:06,830
Being married to an FBI
agent has made you cynical.

435
00:26:07,020 --> 00:26:07,960
It's time for your Insulin,sir.

436
00:26:08,130 --> 00:26:10,310
This has nothing to do with Peter,okay?

437
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:11,990
- I was fooled too.
- I'm offended,Elizabeth!

438
00:26:12,160 --> 00:26:13,600
The whole house can hear you.

439
00:26:13,730 --> 00:26:14,440
This is ridiculous.

440
00:26:14,590 --> 00:26:16,810
Patrick should have no problem
consenting to a blood test.

441
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:17,790
You don't believe me?

442
00:26:19,150 --> 00:26:21,120
Fine.Draw the blood right now.

443
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:22,520
I don't need this,Patrick.

444
00:26:23,870 --> 00:26:26,070
She does.How many others
think you're a fool?

445
00:26:29,260 --> 00:26:31,100
I won't stick a needle into my own son.

446
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:34,580
Okay.I'll do it.

447
00:26:45,630 --> 00:26:49,120
There.Test it.

448
00:27:02,460 --> 00:27:05,980
The house is equidistant from the
avenues,but we don't want him to get that far.

449
00:27:06,420 --> 00:27:09,140
Entry and exit points of the
Wolcott residence,upper windows too.

450
00:27:09,650 --> 00:27:13,500
We're gonna have three agents by the utility van,two more undercover...
- Three more.

451
00:27:15,870 --> 00:27:17,930
Look,Peter,you're a biohazard.

452
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:23,330
I'm on the mend.I
swear.And after this...

453
00:27:24,060 --> 00:27:25,650
- What is it?
- I don't know.

454
00:27:26,140 --> 00:27:28,860
- Mozzie gave it to me.
- Oh,God.

455
00:27:33,350 --> 00:27:37,600
It works.I'm in on this
bust.My wife is in there.

456
00:27:40,590 --> 00:27:43,540
- When it all goes down,we'll move in for the arrest.
- Good boy.

457
00:27:43,830 --> 00:27:44,790
Come on,Chauncey.

458
00:27:45,710 --> 00:27:47,090
It looks like Mozzie's
tincture's working.

459
00:27:48,260 --> 00:27:49,340
I'm coming off the DL.

460
00:27:50,270 --> 00:27:51,680
Baseball.Disabled list.

461
00:27:52,010 --> 00:27:54,010
Did you check out the lab
they used to test the blood?

462
00:27:54,310 --> 00:27:58,560
It's reputable.I put an agent there
in case Patrick tried anything.

463
00:27:59,070 --> 00:28:00,910
William had the sample
picked up from the house.

464
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:03,330
I sealed it and handed it
to the technician myself.

465
00:28:03,770 --> 00:28:05,540
So Patrick didn't tamper with it.

466
00:28:05,690 --> 00:28:08,730
No,but I'm sure he has something planned
when the DNA comes back a mismatch.

467
00:28:09,090 --> 00:28:11,130
I want to know what it is.Audio.

468
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:14,300
Check one,two.Check one,two.

469
00:28:16,930 --> 00:28:18,080
I'll keep an eye on Elizabeth.

470
00:28:19,300 --> 00:28:22,980
Come on,Chaunce.Come
on.That's a good boy.

471
00:28:28,190 --> 00:28:30,030
Everything all right,Miss Bea?

472
00:28:30,350 --> 00:28:31,370
The blood tests are back.

473
00:28:33,530 --> 00:28:36,580
What we have here,Carlyle,is
a real moment of truth.

474
00:28:38,950 --> 00:28:42,130
Everyone,I have news,and
you need to hear it.

475
00:28:42,780 --> 00:28:45,640
You've all been working very hard
to prepare for the party on Sunday,

476
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:47,710
but there's been a change of plans.

477
00:28:48,510 --> 00:28:51,990
The celebration will
now take place tomorrow.

478
00:28:52,810 --> 00:28:56,390
I don't want to wait any
longer to welcome home my son.

479
00:28:58,200 --> 00:28:59,560
I'm so glad to be back.

