00:29:01,080 --> 00:29:02,520
I shouldn't have put you through this.

481
00:29:02,940 --> 00:29:03,840
The DNA was a match.

482
00:29:04,150 --> 00:29:07,310
Also I want to thank Elizabeth
for all that she's done.

483
00:29:07,690 --> 00:29:09,430
Today is her last day.

484
00:29:10,420 --> 00:29:11,940
William,I'm sorry.

485
00:29:12,160 --> 00:29:15,890
- You know I was just thinking of you and Bea.
- The days I have left with my son are numbered.

486
00:29:16,420 --> 00:29:21,470
Forcing him to do this,he could have walked
out the door,and it would have been your fault.

487
00:29:22,170 --> 00:29:23,470
I'll send your check.

488
00:29:27,770 --> 00:29:28,960
What did I do?

489
00:29:38,150 --> 00:29:41,590
Well,I'm fired,and you don't
have to be a butler anymore.

490
00:29:41,770 --> 00:29:42,980
I can't just leave.

491
00:29:43,820 --> 00:29:46,110
Maybe I'll see how French
that maid really is.

492
00:29:48,970 --> 00:29:53,360
Liz.I tried to talk to my father,but
you know how stubborn he is.

493
00:29:53,530 --> 00:29:55,410
Well,he's upset with me,and
I can understand that.

494
00:29:55,570 --> 00:29:56,830
I already took Chauncey on his walk.

495
00:29:57,070 --> 00:29:59,720
Well,I heard him coughing.

496
00:29:59,870 --> 00:30:00,970
I'm gonna take him to the vet.

497
00:30:00,970 --> 00:30:02,990
Well,if he's not feeling
well,he shouldn't walk.

498
00:30:03,180 --> 00:30:05,160
- It's not far.
- It is if he can't breathe.

499
00:30:05,230 --> 00:30:07,320
Don't worry.I'll drive them.

500
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:10,520
I'll get the car.Good day,Mrs.Burke.

501
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:13,120
Take care,Patrick.

502
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:16,350
You too,Liz.

503
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:36,580
- Wait here,and don't move the car.
- Yes,sir.

504
00:30:50,130 --> 00:30:52,540
Hey,Peter.Patrick hates the dog.

505
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:53,880
Now he's bringing it to the vet.

506
00:30:54,060 --> 00:30:54,820
I heard.You're wired.

507
00:30:55,030 --> 00:30:57,490
You've gone from My Man
Godfrey to Ace Ventura.

508
00:30:57,700 --> 00:30:59,090
I'm telling you,he's got another move.

509
00:30:59,270 --> 00:31:05,060
- Neal,recon only.You find anything,you pull me in.
- You got it.

510
00:31:40,170 --> 00:31:42,550
I feel good.Really good.

511
00:31:42,860 --> 00:31:44,750
Great.You and the Wolcotts' dog.

512
00:31:45,040 --> 00:31:46,560
Patrick went to the vet for himself.

513
00:31:47,060 --> 00:31:49,110
I watched the tech remove
something from his arm right here.

514
00:31:49,290 --> 00:31:49,790
- Plastic?
- Yeah.

515
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:53,810
- Look like a vein?
- I don't know.It was about 2/3 this size.

516
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,050
That's a Penrose drain.

517
00:31:55,620 --> 00:31:59,660
There was a case in Florida-- a guy
implanted one to fool a DNA test.

518
00:31:59,890 --> 00:32:02,020
- Filled with someone else's blood?
- Yeah.

519
00:32:02,100 --> 00:32:03,930
That's why Patrick drew his own.

520
00:32:04,330 --> 00:32:05,600
This blood was fresh.

521
00:32:06,110 --> 00:32:10,950
Which means 48 hours ago the
real Patrick Wolcott was alive.

522
00:32:11,120 --> 00:32:13,450
And in New York.You know,we're
kind of good at this.

523
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:18,520
- What?
- William's signing over the trust fund tomorrow.

524
00:32:19,940 --> 00:32:21,990
And once fake Patrick
gets what he wants...

525
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:27,380
- he won't have any reason to keep the real Patrick around.
- No.

526
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:36,900
We pulled in the vet tech.

527
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:39,170
Of course he denies
implanting a Penrose drain.

528
00:32:39,840 --> 00:32:41,970
We searched the property.No
signs of the tubing.

529
00:32:42,050 --> 00:32:44,500
We're holding him on suspicion
so he can't tip Patrick off?

530
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:45,520
You better believe it.

531
00:32:46,100 --> 00:32:50,140
Well,we won't get a warrant for another DNA
testing without permission from the family.

532
00:32:50,330 --> 00:32:53,070
Why don't we just grab the bastard
and tell him we know about the drain?

533
00:32:53,260 --> 00:32:55,040
Tempting,but we have no leverage.

534
00:32:55,210 --> 00:32:56,120
So let's get some leverage.

535
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:57,320
How do we do that?

536
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:00,470
Picasso.

537
00:33:01,890 --> 00:33:03,280
Yeah,yeah,Picasso.

538
00:33:06,610 --> 00:33:09,700
All right,our imposter learned
everything he could about Patrick's life.

539
00:33:09,860 --> 00:33:12,870
But he didn't know Elizabeth's Picasso
story,which proves he doesn't know everything.

540
00:33:13,030 --> 00:33:14,740
Yeah,and he doesn't know
what he doesn't know.

541
00:33:14,890 --> 00:33:19,820
We need to ask him something that he thinks
only the real Patrick knows the answer to.

542
00:33:20,000 --> 00:33:21,710
And give him a reason
to get that answer.

543
00:33:21,890 --> 00:33:26,010
Elizabeth asks him about Picasso--
the next morning he knows everything.

544
00:33:27,890 --> 00:33:28,660
The bike rides.

545
00:33:29,460 --> 00:33:31,600
He goes on one every
morning.It's always for an hour.

546
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:33,190
That's got to be how he's
keeping Patrick alive.

547
00:33:33,340 --> 00:33:35,610
- And how he got the Picasso story.
- And the blood.

548
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:39,640
Jones,get a radius set up in op
- car,bike,foot,whatever.

549
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:42,500
Make sure we stay on him wherever he goes.
- Gotcha.

550
00:33:44,890 --> 00:33:46,670
Patrick was gone for 15 years.

551
00:33:46,870 --> 00:33:48,590
He probably didn't meet
the imposter right away.

552
00:33:48,740 --> 00:33:52,180
The first time he was spotted after he ran
away from boarding school was at Dusseldorf.

553
00:33:52,350 --> 00:33:54,660
And that's where Leo Kovak comes in.

554
00:33:54,830 --> 00:33:56,210
Who is Leo Kovak?

555
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:58,380
He's the reason fake Patrick
has to get the answer.

556
00:33:58,540 --> 00:34:00,420
Who is Leo Kovak?

557
00:34:01,310 --> 00:34:02,900
I'm Leo Kovak?

558
00:34:03,090 --> 00:34:05,910
You are a very angry Croatian.

559
00:34:06,150 --> 00:34:09,890
You work for the Von Kesslers,and you want
to know what the hell happened in Dusseldorf.

560
00:34:10,060 --> 00:34:11,570
What happened in Dusseldorf?

561
00:34:11,710 --> 00:34:14,140
It's--it's got to
be more convincing.

562
00:34:14,300 --> 00:34:15,300
What happened in Dusseldorf?

563
00:34:15,500 --> 00:34:17,690
Nothing.But Patrick doesn't know that.

564
00:34:18,260 --> 00:34:19,510
Croatians invented neckties,

565
00:34:19,660 --> 00:34:22,130
and I'm sure you've got something in
your closet that screams enraged Balkan.

566
00:34:22,340 --> 00:34:24,770
I can't do Croatian.I'm going Polish.

567
00:34:25,500 --> 00:34:26,410
Let's pick out that tie.

568
00:34:33,850 --> 00:34:34,860
Mr.Kovak is here to see you.

569
00:34:36,720 --> 00:34:38,730
I'm a friend of the Von Kesslers.

570
00:34:40,160 --> 00:34:42,690
Of course.The Von Kesslers.

571
00:34:43,080 --> 00:34:45,090
It's been a while since Dusseldorf.

572
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,200
Thank you,Carlyle.

573
00:34:53,730 --> 00:34:57,740
I followed you and your
story in the papers,Patrick.

574
00:34:59,380 --> 00:35:00,860
That's how we found you.

575
00:35:02,620 --> 00:35:05,900
- I'm sorry.Do I...
- You should be sorry for what you did.

576
00:35:07,150 --> 00:35:08,440
Sir,I don't understand.

577
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:12,480
Don't play stupid.Don't start crying.

578
00:35:12,630 --> 00:35:15,380
The Von Kesslers pay me
to handle their problems.

579
00:35:18,810 --> 00:35:23,020
Is there any way I can pay
them for this inconvenience?

580
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:24,970
You think you can put
a price on what you did?

581
00:35:26,050 --> 00:35:27,960
That money can make this go away?

582
00:35:28,100 --> 00:35:31,010
No.They want answers.

583
00:35:33,470 --> 00:35:34,710
Compliments of the chef.

584
00:35:36,680 --> 00:35:37,690
Anything else,sir?

585
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:40,340
A pen and something to write.

586
00:35:52,110 --> 00:35:56,000
Call me.We can make Dusseldorf go away.

587
00:35:57,400 --> 00:36:01,160
But if you don't,I'll see
you at your party tonight.

588
00:36:02,470 --> 00:36:03,630
I'll show myself out.

589
00:36:08,460 --> 00:36:09,590
If I may,sir...

590
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:15,010
that threat didn't sound hollow.

591
00:36:16,650 --> 00:36:17,670
I'm going for a bike ride.

592
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:21,020
Enjoy the fresh air.

593
00:36:31,910 --> 00:36:34,270
He's exiting the park
at Morningside and 116th.

594
00:36:39,980 --> 00:36:40,930
I've got him.

595
00:36:46,410 --> 00:36:48,160
I wouldn't peg you
for a fed in this car.

596
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:50,450
Perimeter is all set.

597
00:36:51,190 --> 00:36:53,010
We'll pinch Patrick at the location.

598
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:55,770
While we're waiting,may I...

599
00:37:02,830 --> 00:37:03,850
Thanks,Leo.

600
00:37:09,690 --> 00:37:11,410
North on Manhattan.Handing off.

601
00:37:19,650 --> 00:37:20,770
Listen to that!

602
00:37:30,290 --> 00:37:31,210
Hard turn,114th.

603
00:37:39,310 --> 00:37:41,280
Agent down!We lost the suspect!

604
00:37:44,180 --> 00:37:45,840
- Neal,get out.
- I'm a butler.

605
00:37:46,700 --> 00:37:47,610
I'm trained for this.

606
00:37:54,180 --> 00:37:58,180
Call an ambulance.All agents to
First Avenue and 114th street.

607
00:37:58,380 --> 00:38:00,620
Agent Burke and Caffrey are en route.

608
00:38:00,890 --> 00:38:04,040
- Team two has him.West on 116th.
- This is 116th.

609
00:38:04,740 --> 00:38:05,470
Neal.

610
00:38:08,750 --> 00:38:09,940
- Neal.
- Don't look.

611
00:38:10,650 --> 00:38:11,910
I have to look.I can't help it.

612
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:15,490
There he goes.

613
00:38:20,990 --> 00:38:24,720
Lost sight of the suspect at the
corner of Morningside and 115th.

614
00:38:26,820 --> 00:38:28,200
That must be some butler college.

615
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:37,220
Where's he keeping Patrick?

616
00:38:38,260 --> 00:38:39,360
He was just here.

617
00:38:39,500 --> 00:38:40,700
Got to be somewhere close.

618
00:38:41,050 --> 00:38:42,840
All right,we're gonna
have to go door to door.

619
00:38:44,160 --> 00:38:48,140
I want a team on this building,down
there,and a team across the street.

620
00:38:49,100 --> 00:38:50,250
Team two,let's go.

621
00:38:53,020 --> 00:38:54,800
- Hey,Peter.
- Yeah,what do you have?

622
00:38:58,470 --> 00:39:02,200
This may be a long shot,but Patrick said
he dropped his travel journal in the Aegean.

623
00:39:03,660 --> 00:39:06,370
Not exactly the Aegean,but
let's have a look.

624
00:39:20,070 --> 00:39:22,070
For the last time,Dusseldorf.

625
00:39:22,450 --> 00:39:23,360
What the hell happened?

626
00:39:23,540 --> 00:39:25,020
Nothing happened in Dusseldorf.

627
00:39:25,150 --> 00:39:28,540
The Von Kesslers are pissed,and
this Kovaks guy is coming after you.

628
00:39:28,710 --> 00:39:30,240
I don't know any of these people.

629
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:34,570
Okay,fine.Fine.We'll
do this the hard way.

630
00:39:35,560 --> 00:39:38,080
The hard way is what's gonna happen
if you don't put that taser down.

631
00:39:38,340 --> 00:39:41,140
Peter Burke,FBI.Cuff him.

632
00:39:44,590 --> 00:39:45,880
- I'm not a butler.
- Let's go.

633
00:39:53,540 --> 00:39:55,530
Everything's gonna be okay,all right?

634
00:40:03,690 --> 00:40:05,170
- Patrick.
- Dad.

635
00:40:16,550 --> 00:40:20,690
I wanted him to be you so
much,I let myself believe.

636
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:23,130
I'm sorry.

637
00:40:24,310 --> 00:40:25,620
I'm sorry I let him into our lives.

638
00:40:29,640 --> 00:40:30,170
Liz.

639
00:40:36,010 --> 00:40:37,900
Bea?

640
00:40:38,580 --> 00:40:42,100
You should know,I'm used
to being an only child.

641
00:41:03,660 --> 00:41:07,760
Patrick and Keith- that's his
real name-- met on Santorini.

642
00:41:08,480 --> 00:41:10,220
People said they could
pass for brothers.

643
00:41:10,970 --> 00:41:14,900
When Patrick decided to come
home,Keith offered to come with him.

644
00:41:15,650 --> 00:41:18,770
He took Patrick
hostage,read his journals.

645
00:41:19,010 --> 00:41:20,340
That man stole his life.

646
00:41:21,150 --> 00:41:22,380
And now he's got it back again.

647
00:41:22,440 --> 00:41:24,380
- Thanks to you.
- Thanks to us.

648
00:41:27,310 --> 00:41:30,720
Are you up for some...some baseball?

649
00:41:30,910 --> 00:41:34,280
- A night game?
- Yeah.I figured we could pick up where we left off.

650
00:41:34,520 --> 00:41:40,030
I could
probably-- Oh,no.

651
00:41:40,380 --> 00:41:42,550
Damn it.I'll call Mozzie.

652
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:48,110
Wait,wait,wait,hold on.If you've had
this flu already,I think we're safe.

